==Production==
The shooting of the film started on 25 April 2014 in [[Cape Town, South Africa]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/akshay-kumar-lisa-haydon-start-shooting-for-shaukeen-remake/|title=Akshay Kumar, Lisa Haydon start shooting for 'Shaukeen' remake |newspaper= The Indian Express|accessdate=28 April 2014}}</ref> The indoor scenes were shot in a hotel room. Next schedule of filming started in [[Mauritius]] in early May 2014. The next schedule began in [[Delhi]] in May itself.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/screen/akshay-kumars-shaukeen-remake-kicks-off/|title=Akshay Kumar's 'Shaukeen' remake kicks off|newspaper=The Indian Express|accessdate=3 May 2014}}</ref> [[Anupam Kher]] twitted that he was going to Delhi for outdoor shooting in Delhi on 11 May 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/anupam-kher-in-delhi-for-shaukeen-shoot/|title=Anupam Kher in Delhi for 'Shaukeen' shoot|newspaper=Indian Express|accessdate=11 May 2014}}</ref> Last schedule was shot in [[cape town]] in August 2014. 

Musical artist [[Yo Yo Honey Singh|Honey Singh]] was signed for a song in the film. Singh has earlier collaborated with [[Akshay Kumar]] a few times, and on his request to the rapper-performer for one special number for the film, Singh offered him three songs for the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-honey-singh-offers-bonanza-for-akshay-kumar-s-shaukeen-1981510|title=Honey Singh offers bonanza for Akshay Kumar's 'Shaukeen'|newspaper=DNA}}</ref>

Initially, [[Nargis Fakhri]] was signed for the film but when she  left the project for a Hollywood film, ''Spy''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://movies.ndtv.com/bollywood/akshay-kumar-to-romance-nargis-fakhri-in-shaukeen-remake-371856|title=Akshay Kumar to romance Nargis Fakhri in Shaukeen remake|newspaper=NDTV|accessdate=27 May 2013}}</ref> the role was offered to [[Shraddha Kapoor]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/shraddha-kapoor-to-replace-nargis-fakhri-for-shaukeen-remake/article1-1195146.aspx|title=Shraddha Kapoor to replace Nargis Fakhri for Shaukeen remake|newspaper=hindustantimes|accessdate=14 March 2014}}</ref> The part was finally offered to [[Lisa Haydon]] who accepted it. It was her first solo heroine film.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/1141011/jsp/t2/story_18913516.jsp|title=Lisa Haydon is Ahana in the Shaukeens after being Vijaylakshmi in Queen|work=The Telegraph|access-date=2018-06-26}}</ref> [[Akshay Kumar]] was signed to play partner of Ahana played by Haydon, a role which [[Mithun Chakraborty]] had portrayed in the original film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news-interviews/Nargis-Fakhri-dropped-from-Shaukeen-remake/articleshow/31871899.cms|title=Nargis Fakhri dropped from Shaukeen remake|newspaper=timesofindia|accessdate=12 March 2014}}</ref>

==Soundtrack==
The songs in the film are composed by [[Yo Yo Honey Singh]], [[Arko Pravo Mukherjee|Arko]], [[Hard Kaur]] & Vikram Negi. The [[film score]] is composed by [[Sandeep Chowta]].

